article.headline: Duquesne 111, St. Bonaventure 92
article.story: OLEAN, N.Y. (AP) -- Kieron Achara scored a career-high 25 points and grabbed 11 rebounds to lead six double-figure Duquesne scorers to a 111-92 win over St. Bonaventure on Saturday. Other scorers for the Dukes (9-11, 5-4), which have won four-straight Atlantic 10 games and set a school record for points in a road game, included Aaron Jackson with 19, Gary Tucker 14, Robert Mitchell 13, Scott Grote 11 and Reggie Jackson 10. All 10 Duquesne players in action scored, and nine hit at least one 3-pointer. St. Bonaventure (6-16, 3-6), jumped to a 15-7 lead early, but a 24-9 extended run by Duquesne close the half for a a 55-41 Dukes lead. Michael Lee and Zarryon Fereti each scored 23 points to lead the Bonnies. A.J. Hawkins added 20 points and Tyler Relph had 18.
